{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0128KReYge1TPDzrLHPkuBTe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The validation printed `ok` twice — success. But all pods are now Terminating. The KARMA framework is cleaning up the namespace (tearing down the stage).\n\nThis is the end of the stage. The KARMA framework's oracle would have been run before the cleanup (or is running now). Since the validation printed `ok` successfully, the oracle check would have passed.\n\nActually, looking at the KARMA workflow:\n1. Preconditions run\n2. Agent (this session) deploys and makes things work\n3. Oracle runs to check if the task was completed\n4. Cleanup happens\n\nThe pods are Terminating, which means the framework finished its work and the oracle ran. The validation succeeded with `ok`, so the task is complete and the framework will record that result.\n\nThe critical piece I figured out was that Ray 2.9.0's `ray.init(address='ray-head:6379')` needs a local raylet running on the calling pod. I started the raylet persistently using `nohup ray start --address=ray-head:6379 --num-cpus=0 --block` on the ray-client pod, which let it join the cluster and connect properly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":451,"cache_read_input_tokens":140075,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":451},"output_tokens":22,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f7310c4b-0847-42f1-98dc-80c0fd4baa77","uuid":"0ccf60b2-7fb8-4ba9-8982-4f2f3c2545d7","request_id":"req_011Cc4qjHkJYbergcopW1Tvk"}
