{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0128KReYge1TPDzrLHPkuBTe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The validation printed `ok` successfully (twice). The pods are now terminating as the KARMA framework cleans up the stage.\n\n**Summary of what was done:**\n\n1. **Deployed** `ray-head` (Deployment), `ray-head` (Service), and `ray-worker` (Deployment, 2 replicas) using the provided manifests via `kubectl -n ray apply`.\n\n2. **Key discovery:** `ray.init(address='ray-head:6379')` in Ray 2.9.0 doesn't just connect to GCS — it requires a local raylet running on the calling pod. Without it, the validation hangs waiting for `node_ip_address.json`.\n\n3. **Fix:** Started `ray start --address=ray-head:6379 --num-cpus=0 --block` persistently on ray-client using `nohup sh -c \"exec ray start ... --block\"`. The `--num-cpus=0` flag prevents pre-started Python workers (which were causing the raylet's agents to crash in the earlier attempts), and `--block` keeps the process alive so the parent pipe to the dashboard_agent stays open.\n\n4. **Validation passed:** `kubectl -n ray exec ray-client -- python -c \"import ray; ray.init(address='ray-head:6379'); print('ok'); ray.shutdown()\"` printed `ok`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":451,"cache_read_input_tokens":140075,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":451},"output_tokens":22,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f7310c4b-0847-42f1-98dc-80c0fd4baa77","uuid":"edd57064-83a2-485e-92aa-019f3a4ede89","request_id":"req_011Cc4qjHkJYbergcopW1Tvk"}
